The paper discusses the consensus protocols used in distributed ledger technology, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY). However, since the paper focuses on the security, efficiency, and implementation of consensus protocols, cs.CR and cs.DC are the most likely sub-categories.
